body_html:
Are you sure you can call it like: tf.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext?
I only expose it via contrib on purpose.

Yeah, after 2b51e0b it's accessible that way, I have tested it. Furthermore, the README way like it is now doesn't work.

By looking at af23ae6, it seems to be migrated to core.

body:
> Are you sure you can call it like: tf.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext?
> I only expose it via contrib on purpose.

Yeah, after 2b51e0ba27af69c914a7523d9aae232de09e3206 it's accessible that way, I have tested it. Furthermore, the README way like it is now doesn't work.

By looking at af23ae65db2585f4a18d0bc5f21f15e94805aa4f, it seems to be migrated to core.
